{
  "id": "019cdcdc-fd00-7850-9bc2-a9a8d5dcfdc5",
  "content": "       let chunks = pipeline.process(\"Some text content.\", &test_meta(\"txt\")).unwrap();\n        assert_eq!(chunks[0].processing.strategy_name, \"fallback\");\n        assert!(!chunks[0].processing.was_split);\n        assert!(!chunks[0].processing.was_merged);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Register module and run tests to verify they fail**\n\nAdd to `crates/corvia-kernel/src/lib.rs` after `pub mod chunking_fallback;`:\n```rust\npub mod chunking_pipeline;\n```\n\nRun: `cargo test -p corvia-kernel chunking_pipeline -- --nocapture`\nExpected: FAIL (todo!() panics)\n\n**Step 3: Implement ChunkingPipeline**\n\nImplement `process()` and `process_batch()` following the design doc's pipeline steps:\n\n1. Resolve strategy via registry\n2. Call `strategy.chunk()`\n3. Kernel default merge: combine adjacent chunks where both are below `min_tokens` and combined fits `max_tokens`\n4. Enforce budget: for each chunk exceeding `max_tokens`, call `strategy.split_oversized()`, recurse until all fit\n5. Overlap: if `overlap_tokens > 0`, prepend trailing text from previous chunk\n6. Build `ProcessedChunk` with token estimates and processing info\n\nThe merge pass should respect `merge_group` metadata — only merge chunks with the same `merge_group` (or both `None`). The strategy's `merge_small()` override takes priority if it returns `Some`.\n\n**Step 4: Run tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p corvia-kernel chunking_pipeline -- --nocapture`\nExpected: All tests PASS\n\nRun: `cargo test -p corvia-kernel -- --nocapture` (full crate)\nExpected: All tests PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add crates/corvia-kernel/src/chunking_pipeline.rs crates/corvia-kernel/src/lib.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(m3.3): ChunkingPipeline + FormatRegistry — kernel orchestrator (D65/D66)\"\n```\n\n---\n",
